<p>I have set up an <a href="http://sphinx-doc.org/latest/ext/intersphinx.html" rel="nofollow">Intersphinx</a>-mapping for the documentations of Python 2 and Python 3:</p>  <pre><code>intersphinx_mapping = {'py2': ('http://docs.python.org/', None),                        'py3': ('http://docs.python.org/3', None)} </code></pre>  <p>How can I reference a class from a specific of these two resources? The documentation only mentions <code>:ref:</code>erences and these two attempts do not work:</p>  <pre><code>:ref:`collections.Mapping &lt;py2:collections.Mapping&gt;` :class:`py3:collections.Mapping` </code></pre>  <p>While this generates an expected link:</p>  <pre><code>:class:`collections.Mapping` </code></pre>